The paper deals with the study and comparison of computational models, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The use of degrees and hierarchies suggests a logical and mathematical approach, which could also fit under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The mention of descriptive set theory and Borel hierarchy suggests a connection to the study of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of analytic computation suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the mention of BSS machines suggests a connection to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL).
